From Scott Barman Subject Re How to speed up games marginally realistic In article Archer Bad Cop Surly writes In m nll S ahC udcps cps udayton edu Michael Bohler writes To really speed up the game umps need to START CALLING STRIKES the way they used to I'm talking about making the strike zone start at the knees and go up to the top of the letters Forget this the strike zone is in the general area of the groin A lot less and counts and a quicker game They tried that in the ' 's and people stopped coming to the ballparks in droves, as offense suffered immensely They lowered the mound first before the season The shrinkage of the strike zone didn't start until the mid s scott barman Mets Mailing List feed the following into your shell mail subscribe Let's Go Mets